How it works
TriggerEvery time there is a commit on a branch.mainOr press manual run.
step:
Checkout repository
Set up Git for the bot.
Copy files from docs/Go to the Wiki repository (.wiki)
Commit and push to Wiki repo.
resultThe Wiki will automatically update to match the documentation whenever there is a commit.

ğŸŒ Key features of this template:
Reusable every year (same standard).
Real-time updates when a commit occurs.
Supports manual triggers for special syncs.
Reduce redundancy: Docs are the primary source of information, Wiki is a mirror for reference.

