âœ… Standard Checklist (Checklist Template)
# Project Checklist

## Basic Information
- [ ] Project ID
- [ ] Project Title
- [ ] Author/Owner
- [ ] Version
- [ ] Last Updated

## Main Content
- [ ] Overview (Project Overview)
- [ ] Objectives (Purpose)
- [ ] Key Findings (Main Analysis Results)
- [ ] Next Steps (Next steps plan)

## Additional Information
- [ ] References (Sources/Links)
- [ ] Queries (data retrieval commands)
- [ ] Attachments (Original file/Cloud link)

## Verification
- [ ] Commit to GitHub
- [ ] Sync to Wiki
- [ ] Reviewed by Team


ğŸ”„ How to use in Workflow
Create a new project.â†’ Copytemplates/Go to the project folder.
Fill out the checklist.â†’ Fill in the information.checklist.mdTo be complete.
Summary Notesâ†’ Usesummary.yamlFor metadata and data structures.
Commitâ†’ Push to GitHub â†’ Actions will automatically sync to the Wiki.
Trace backâ†’ Use the Wiki + checklist to check the project's completeness.

âœ¨ Highlights of this package
have Standard templateFor every project â†’ Reduce confusion.
A checklist helps prevent data loss â†’ Easy to verify.
Wiki mirroring makes it easy to review information â†’ Use it as a reference in conjunction with documentation.
Queries are clearly separated â†’ Data can be retrieved repeatedly without copying files.
ğŸ“˜ User Manual
GuideBlueprint:
id: string # Guide ID, e.g., "streaming-module"
title: string # Guide title, e.g., "Streaming Module Usage Guide"
description: string # Short description (in Thai)
version: string # version, e.g., "v1.0"
author: string # Author/Administrator
last_updated: date # Last modified date
commands: Command[] # List of commands actually used
ethics_banner: string # Safety and ethics banner

Command:
name: string # Command name, e.g., "Start Streaming"
syntax: string # Usage format, e.g., "npm run stream"
description: string # Description (Thai)
example: string # Real-world example usage

ğŸ·ï¸ Title & Description Template
TitleUse the module or topic name, for example:


Streaming Module Usage Guide
Magic Button Quick Reference
DescriptionBriefly explain what this manual is for, for example:


"This guide describes how to use the Streaming module for presenting and sharing multi-stream data."
"This guide provides instructions on using the Magic Button to capture ideas and inspiration."

âš–ï¸ Principles of Data Use
Accuracy
Use the information as recorded in the manual; do not modify it without verification.
Transparency
Always indicate the source of information and provide references.
Responsibility
Users are responsible for the consequences of using the data.
Safety
Do not use this information to violate the rights of, misrepresent, or harm others.
Ethics
Use data for development, learning, and innovation, not for destruction.

ğŸš¨ Ethics & Safety Banner
âš ï¸ **Ethics & Safety Notice**

The information in this guide is part of research and development.
All users must adhere to the following principles:

- Use the information accurately and transparently.
- Take responsibility for the consequences.
- Do not use this information for rights violations or harm.
- Respect the ethics and safety of all parties.

By accessing and using this information, the user agrees to these terms.













